Always provided when you get a piercing from us! Posted @withregram • @safepiercing The best thing you can use to clean your piercing is saline. Pre-made saline in a can is suggested as it's sterile and gentle on your piercing. If saline isn't provided by your piercer, you can find saline in the wound aisle in almost every grocery store and drug store, usually called "wound wash saline."
.
Don't forget that your piercer is always there to assist you if you're having an issue with your piercing. 
.
Happy healing!

I am so sad to hear of Coach Denny Crum’s passing today. Growing up in Louisville he was an absolute legend when I was a kid. In Boy Scouts we would lay out flyers and such in the seats at Freedom Hall then get to stay and watch the games from the top of the nosebleeds. 

Years later when we started our Meghan’s Mountain event at the studio, Coach Crum made several appearances over the years to help us raise money for the charity. He was a personal hero to Meghan, and a dear friend of her family’s. 

My love and thoughts go out to his wife Susan, Meghan’s dad Jerry, and our entire community on this loss. 

^Buddy  #tattoocharlies #prestonhwy #louisville #kentucky #keeplouisvilleweird #bestoflouisville  #tattooswhileyouwait #louisvilletattoo #louisvilleky
